  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity building for meteorological institutes in Oceania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Finnish Meteorological Institute together with the Pacific Regional Environment Programme (SPREP) proposes an ICI project to build capacity of the National Meteorological Services (NMS) in Oseania. The purpose of the project is to strengthen the capacity of the National Meteorological Services in Oceania to produce high quality weather services for their societies in order to address the challenges posed by the climate change and extreme weather phenomena. The project will develop the capacity of the NMS to provide aviation weather services according to quality management systems and help strengthen the needs based customer service. The project also aims to build capacity in SPREP to provide better support to NMS in the implementation of the quality management system and producing weather services. The budget for 2,5 years is 498 979 euros.</narrative>
  </description>
